  description: "AI testing platform that automatically generates test cases, validates prompts, and monitors production LLM performance.",
  fullDescription: "Cheatlayer is a specialized testing and monitoring platform for teams building applications on large language models (LLMs). As LLM-based applications move from prototypes to production, teams face unique quality challenges: prompt changes have unpredictable effects, models degrade or change behavior over time, and traditional unit testing doesn't work with non-deterministic outputs. Cheatlayer solves these problems with automated test generation, prompt validation, and continuous production monitoring. The platform starts by analyzing your application's prompts and expected outputs, then generates hundreds of test cases covering edge scenarios, failure modes, prompt injections, and adversarial inputs. Each test case includes an expected result template (not exact string matching, but semantic evaluation of whether the LLM's response meets criteria like 'contains pricing information' or 'does not hallucinate features'). For prompt engineering teams, Cheatlayer provides A/B testing of prompt versions against test suites, showing exactly how changes affect accuracy, latency, cost, and safety. The production monitoring feature continuously samples live LLM calls, evaluating them against the same criteria and alerting when performance degrades or when the model starts producing unexpected outputs. Cheatlayer supports all major LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Cohere, open-source via Replicate/Together) and can run evaluations on different models to help with model selection decisions. The platform includes cost analysis showing token usage by feature, prompt, or user. For compliance-heavy applications, Cheatlayer maintains audit trails of all test runs and production evaluations. While traditional software testing focuses on deterministic code, LLM applications require probabilistic evaluation—Cheatlayer provides the infrastructure for this new paradigm, helping teams ship AI features with confidence that they won't fail in embarrassing, costly, or dangerous ways. Early customers include fintech, healthcare, and legal tech companies where LLM accuracy isn't just nice-to-have—it's mission-critical.",
  category: "Developer Tools",
  rating: 4.5,
  pricing: "Paid",
