  fullDescription: "Riko is an intelligent meeting assistant that joins video calls (Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, Webex) to automatically transcribe conversations, generate concise summaries, and extract actionable next steps. Unlike manual notetaking where participants divide attention between contributing to discussions and documenting them, Riko handles documentation entirely, allowing all attendees to focus fully on the conversation. The AI joins meetings as a participant (announcing its presence for transparency) and produces a complete transcript with speaker identification, timestamps, and searchable text. After the meeting, Riko generates an executive summary highlighting key decisions, open questions, and discussed topics, plus a separate action item list with assigned owners (inferred from conversation context) and deadlines. The platform integrates with project management tools (Asana, Trello, Jira, Monday.com), CRMs (Salesforce, HubSpot), and collaboration platforms (Slack, Notion), automatically pushing action items into the appropriate systems. For recurring meetings like weekly standups or status updates, Riko learns the regular format and can pre-populate agendas based on previous meetings' pending items. Privacy features include options to pause recording during sensitive discussions, on-premise data storage for enterprise customers, and compliance with GDPR and CCPA. For distributed teams facing 'Zoom fatigue' and information overload from back-to-back meetings, Riko ensures no discussion gets lost and every action item gets tracked. The platform also offers post-meeting analytics showing speaking time distribution (helpful for ensuring inclusive participation) and sentiment trends over time. For managers juggling multiple teams and projects, Riko transforms meeting documentation from a time-consuming burden into an automated, reliable process that keeps everyone aligned and accountable without adding extra work.",
